<<silently>><<set _next_passage to "Ma Rainey 1">><</silently>>

:: Ma Rainey 1 [mrbb nobr]
<p>August Wilson‚Äôs 1982 play <i>Ma Rainey‚Äôs Black Bottom</i> opens in a recording studio, on two white men - Irvin, Ma Rainey‚Äôs agent, and Sturdyvant, the owner of the studio and the record label - testing their technology in advance of a session with Rainey and her band. Irvin hooks up a microphone while Sturdyvant watches from above, ensconced in what the script calls the ‚Äúcontrol booth"<<cite "x" "Wilson, August. Ma Rainey's Black Bottom.">> that is, in most productions, located physically above the main stage, like a prison guard's tower. This distance spatializes Wilson's description of Sturdyvant as a man who is "preoccupied with money... insensitive to black performers and prefers to deal with them at arm's length" <<cite "17" "Wilson, August. Ma Rainey's Black Bottom.">></p>

<<set _slides to ['assets/imgs/mr_nt_set.jpeg', 'assets/imgs/mr_netflix_set.png', 'assets/imgs/mr_wt_set.jpeg']>>
	<figure>
		<img style="width:100%" @src=[_slides[0]]>
