<p>Now, most people who now watch <i>Quad</i> do so on their computers ‚Äì either through a local file, as bits that are themselves translated electrical variances saved locally, or streamed from data saved on a server in a bunker somewhere. Still, traces of the human remain a vital part of the teleplay ‚Äì shuffling bodies invite empathy, identification, disgust, fear, the dancers sometimes shuffle more or less quickly, one can begin to identify secondary gender characteristics under the robes (or, at least, try to). [[A transcoded body is still a body.]]</p>

